// Startup benchmark: a minimal program. The interesting number is NOT printed
// here - the runner times the whole process (build once, then run N times and
// take the fastest wall-clock). Jux is AOT-native with no VM/JIT warmup, so this
// is a decisive win vs Java/C# (ms vs tens-to-hundreds of ms). The program just
// prints a marker so the runner can confirm it ran.
public void main() {
    print("RESULT startup=ok");
}
